 of a spring) and how kinetic energy depends on mass and speed, allow the concept of conserva','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471753',0),(440,'','The availability of energy limits what can occur in any system.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471754',0),(441,'','Uncontrolled systems always evolve toward more stable states—that is, toward more uniform energy distribution (e.g., water flows downhill, objects hotter than their surrounding environment cool down).','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471755',0),(442,'','A bigger push or pull makes things speed up or slow down more quickly.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2468143',0),(443,'','When objects collide, the contact forces transfer energy so as to change the objects\' motions.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2470932',0),(444,'','When two objects interact, each one exerts a force on the other that can cause energy to be transferred to or from the object.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471300',0),(445,'','When two objects interacting through a field change relative position, the energy stored in the field is changed.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471756',0),(446,'','The expression \"produce energy\" typically refers to the conversion of stored energy into a desired form for practical use.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2470933',0),(447,'','The energy released [from] food was once energy from the sun that was captured by plants in the chemical process that forms plant matter (from air and water).','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471084',0),(448,'','The chemical reaction by which plants produce complex food molecules (sugars) requires an energy input (i.e., from sunlight) to occur. In this reaction, carbon dioxide and water combine to form carbon-based organic molecules and release oxygen.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471379',0),(449,'','Cellular respiration in plants and animals involve chemical reactions with oxygen that release stored energy. In these processes, complex molecules containing carbon react with oxygen to produce carbon dioxide and other materials.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471380',0),(450,'','Nuclear Fusion processes in the center of the sun release the energy that ultimately reaches Earth as radiation.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2472009',0),(451,'','Although energy cannot be destroyed, it can be converted to less useful forms—for example, to thermal energy in the surrounding environment.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471757',0),(452,'','Solar cells are human-made devices that likewise capture the sun\'s energy and produce electrical energy.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471793',0),(453,'','The main way that solar energy is captured and stored on Earth is through the complex chemical process known as photosynthesis.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471889',0),(454,'','Sound can make matter vibrate, and vibrating matter can make sound.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2470597',0),(455,'','Waves, which are regular patterns of motion, can be made in water by disturbing the surface. When waves move across the surface of deep water, the water goes up and down in place; there is no net motion in the direction of the wave except when the water m','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2470958',0),(456,'','Waves of the same type can differ in amplitude (height of the wave) and wavelength (spacing between wave peaks).','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2470959',0),(457,'','A simple wave has a repeating pattern with a specific wavelength, frequency, and amplitude.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471327',0),(458,'','A sound wave needs a medium through which it is transmitted.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471328',0),(459,'','The wavelength and frequency of a wave are related to one another by the speed of travel of the wave, which depends on the type of wave and the medium through which it is passing.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471794',0),(460,'