al geography, all of which can affect oceanic and atm','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471563',0),(610,'','Because these patterns are so complex, weather can only be predicted probabilistically.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471564',0),(611,'','The ocean exerts a major influence on weather and climate by absorbing energy from the sun, releasing it over time, and globally redistributing it through ocean currents.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471565',0),(612,'','The foundation for Earth\'s global climate systems is the electromagnetic radiation from the sun, as well as its reflection, absorption, storage, and redistribution among the atmosphere, ocean, and land systems, and this energy\'s re-radiation into space.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2472061',0),(613,'','Gradual atmospheric changes were due to plants and other organisms that captured carbon dioxide and released oxygen.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2472062',0),(614,'','Changes in the atmosphere due to human activity have increased carbon dioxide concentrations and thus affect climate.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2472063',0),(615,'','Current models predict that, although future regional climate changes will be complex and varied, average global temperatures will continue to rise. The outcomes predicted by global climate models strongly depend on the amounts of human-generated greenhou','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2472110',0),(616,'','Plants and animals can change their environment.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2470547',0),(617,'','Living things affect the physical characteristics of their regions.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2471011',0),(618,'','The many dynamic and delicate feedbacks between the biosphere and other Earth systems cause a continual co-evolution of Earth\'s surface and the life that exists on it.','http://asn.jesandco.org/resources/S2472064',0),(619,'','Living things need water, air, and resources from the land, and they live 