,0,'http://localhost.localdomain/?page_id=11',0,'page','',0),(12,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:16','2019-04-12 15:07:16','Through a classroom game and resource handouts, students learn about the techniques used in persuasive oral arguments and apply them to independent persuasive writing activities.','Can You Convince Me? Developing Persuasive Writing','','publish','open','closed','','can_you_convince_me_developing_persuasive_writing','','','2019-04-12 15:07:16','2019-04-12 15:07:16','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/can_you_convince_me_developing_persuasive_writing/',0,'resource','',0),(13,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:16','2019-04-12 15:07:16','Developing a sense of hundredths through the use of models In this series of 3 hands-on activities, students develop and reinforce their understanding of hundredths as fractions, decimals, and percentages. Students explore using candy pieces as they physically make and connect a set/linear model to area models.','A Meter of Candy','','publish','open','closed','','a_meter_of_candy','','','2019-04-12 15:07:16','2019-04-12 15:07:16','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/a_meter_of_candy/',0,'resource','',0),(14,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:16','2019-04-12 15:07:16','In this animated video segment adapted from NASA, astronomer Doris Daou explains how the forces of speed and gravity keep the Moon in a constant orbit around Earth.','Why Doesn\'t the Moon Fall Down?','','publish','open','closed','','why_doesnt_the_moon_fall_down','','','2019-04-12 15:07:16','2019-04-12 15:07:16','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/why_doesnt_the_moon_fall_down/',0,'resource','',0),(15,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:17','2019-04-12 15:07:17','What do plants eat? This unit explores plants and how they make food.','Plants','','publish','open','closed','','plants','','','2019-04-12 15:07:17','2019-04-12 15:07:17','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/plants/',0,'resource','',0),(16,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:17','2019-04-12 15:07:17','shows daily (back to June 16 1995