rce/creating_an_immigrant_scorecard_-_creating_a_formula/',0,'resource','',0),(41,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:23','2019-04-12 15:07:23','Juxtaposing the architecture of Ellis island with that of the proposed Trump Wall creates many opportunities for mathematical analysis and frames a discussion of how our nation\'s attitude toward immigration has changed','From Ellis Island to the Trump Wall - A Mathematical Analysis','','publish','open','closed','','from_ellis_island_to_the_trump_wall_-_a_mathematical_analysis_','','','2019-04-12 15:07:23','2019-04-12 15:07:23','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/from_ellis_island_to_the_trump_wall_-_a_mathematical_analysis_/',0,'resource','',0),(42,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:24','2019-04-12 15:07:24','In this third lesson of the four part series, students briefly examine the 2002 famine in Africa and the factors that contributed to its severity, with a special focus on Malawi.','The Dark Horse Comes to Malawi: Famine in Africa','','publish','open','closed','','the_dark_horse_comes_to_malawi_famine_in_africa','','','2019-04-12 15:07:24','2019-04-12 15:07:24','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/the_dark_horse_comes_to_malawi_famine_in_africa/',0,'resource','',0),(43,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:24','2019-04-12 15:07:24','How do we establish and maintain a colony on Mars? As the 10th grade capstone experience, students will create a Mars society that incorporates learning from core curricular areas. The project will culminate in a recruitment fair where students will convince stakeholders to join their colony.','Creating a Constitution for a Colony on Mars','','publish','open','closed','','creating_a_constitution_for_a_colony_on_mars','','','2019-04-12 15:07:24','2019-04-12 15:07:24','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/creating_a_constitution_for_a_colony_on_mars/',0,'resource','',0),(44,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:24','2019-04-12 15:07:24','Offers several pictures of 10 buildings of the famous American architect, as well as discussion of his life and work. The site offers films clips of Wright being interviewed.','Frank Lloyd Wright','','publish','open','closed','','frank_lloyd_wright','','','2019-04-12 15:07:24','2019-04-12 15:07:24','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/frank_lloyd_wright/',0,'resource','',0),(45,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:25','2019-04-12 15:07:25','When visiting the recommended website in this lesson, students learn about the Underground Railroad and \"walk in the shoes\" of an escaping slave. Using the picture book Sweet Clara and the Freedom Quilt, students create a problems/solutions/events chart to help them understand the relationships between Clara\'s problems and how she solves them. Similar to Clara\'s map that shows the path north to freedom, students create their own map, designing a key, a compass, and landmarks surrounding their home and school.','Escaping Slavery: Sweet Clara and the Freedom Quilt','','publish','open','closed','','escaping_slavery_sweet_clara_and_the_freedom_quilt','','','2019-04-12 15:07:25','2019-04-12 15:07:25','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/escaping_slavery_sweet_clara_and_the_freedom_quilt/',0,'resource','',0),(46,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:25','2019-04-12 15:07:25','Students will learn what it means to be a U.S. citizen and how citizenship is obtained. They will compare and contrast personal and political rights with social responsibilities and personal duties. Students will explore global citizenship, and the rights and responsibilities of citizens in other countries. They will also learn about community engagement by selecting a problem of their own and creating a plan to solve it.','Citizenship and Participation','','publish','open','closed','','citizenship_and_participation_','','','2019-04-12 15:07:25','2019-04-12 15:07:25','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/citizenship_and_participation_/',0,'resource','',0),(47,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:25','2019-04-12 15:07:25',' An Introduction to 6th Grade Social Studies With Lesson 6, students move away from the study of individuals to the study of groups of people. An investigation of world history is ultimately an exploration of how groups of people formed communities, cultures, and civilizations. ','What is Community','','publish','open','closed','','what_is_community','','','2019-04-12 15:07:25','2019-04-12 15:07:25','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/what_is_community/',0,'resource','',0),(48,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:25','2019-04-12 15:07:25','After this lesson, students will have learned about the life and work of Martin Luther King, Jr. reflected on a section of King\'s \"I Have a Dream\" speech become aware of inequities that still exist in the United States ','Dr. Kings Dream','','publish','open','closed','','dr-_kings_dream','','','2019-04-12 15:07:25','2019-04-12 15:07:25','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/dr-_kings_dream/',0,'resource','',0),(49,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:26','2019-04-12 15:07:26','Students will analyze the concept of procedural justice by: identifying in a play the unfair decisions by the ruler, stating the procedural guarantees that ought to be included in a Bill of Rights, comparing their list of procedural guarantees to the procedural guarantees provided by the U.S. Constitution and Bill of Rights, and concluding that procedural fairness is an essential element of the Bill of Rights.','Judges in the Classroom Lesson Plan','','publish','open','closed','','judges_in_the_classroom_lesson_plan','','','2019-04-12 15:07:26','2019-04-12 15:07:26','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/judges_in_the_classroom_lesson_plan/',0,'resource','',0),(50,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:26','2019-04-12 15:07:26','This unit focuses on the rule of law and the impartiality of the courts, requiring students to act as a jury, writing and presenting arguments. In the book No, David! by David Shannon, a young man who is known for getting into trouble has been accused of theft. The class engages in a mock trial, character analysis, argument writing, and serves as a jury for this case.','Introduction to the Rule of Law','','publish','open','closed','','introduction_to_the_rule_of_law','','','2019-04-12 15:07:26','2019-04-12 15:07:26','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/introduction_to_the_rule_of_law/',0,'resource','',0),(51,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:26','2019-04-12 15:07:26','This is the last lesson in the unit designed to teach the significance of the U.S. Constitution and the shared powers of government and the United States Constitution. Focus on this lesson is on the differences among federal, state, and local governments. ','The Responsibilities of Local Government','','publish','open','closed','','the_responsibilities_of_local_government','','','2019-04-12 15:07:26','2019-04-12 15:07:26','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/the_responsibilities_of_local_government/',0,'resource','',0),(52,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:26','2019-04-12 15:07:26','This library of mini-lessons targets a variety of landmark cases from the United States Supreme Court. Each mini-lesson includes a one-page reading and a one-page activity, and is appropriate for a variety of uses. Unlike the iCivics lesson plans, these mini-lessons are designed for students to complete independently without the need for teacher direction.','Landmark Library','','publish','open','closed','','landmark_library_','','','2019-04-12 15:07:26','2019-04-12 15:07:26','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/landmark_library_/',0,'resource','',0),(53,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:26','2019-04-12 15:07:26',' This unit is designed to provide students with an introduction to the electoral processes of the American political system. Students will develop a strong foundation that will inform them of their choices and encourage civic involvement. The Politics and Public Policy unit guides students to a deep understanding of concepts and processes through simulations, presentations, vocabulary-building activities and a mock election.','Polotics and Public Policy','','publish','open','closed','','polotics_and_public_policy_','','','2019-04-12 15:07:26','2019-04-12 15:07:26','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/polotics_and_public_policy_/',0,'resource','',0),(54,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:26','2019-04-12 15:07:26','This third grade lesson is part of a Government and Citizenship unit. This unit is designed for students to understand that communities and nations need laws and leaders to help protect citizens and keep order, and that our government relies on participation from its citizens. The students will focus on why  citizens need laws and leaders, what laws and leaders do, and how citizens help governments. ','American Heroes','','publish','open','closed','','american_heroes','','','2019-04-12 15:07:26','2019-04-12 15:07:26','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/american_heroes/',0,'resource','',0),(55,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:27','2019-04-12 15:07:27','At the time the Founders were shaping the future of a new country, John Adams suggested the President should be addressed as H\"is Excellency\" Happily, others recognized that such a title was inappropriate. Though the proper form of address represents only a small detail, defining everything about the Presidency was central to the idea of America that was a work-in-progress when the nation was young.','Starting a Government from Scratch','','publish','open','closed','','starting_a_government_from_scratch','','','2019-04-12 15:07:27','2019-04-12 15:07:27','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/starting_a_government_from_scratch/',0,'resource','',0),(56,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:27','2019-04-12 15:07:27','Mini-Mock Trials are shorter versions of mock trial, taking an average of 2-3 hours. They are helpful for teaching about trial procedure as well as teaching the particular content of the trial. For example, one mini mock trial teaches driving responsibility. ','Mini Mock Trial','','publish','open','closed','','mini_mock_trial','','','2019-04-12 15:07:27','2019-04-12 15:07:27','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/mini_mock_trial/',0,'resource','',0),(57,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:27','2019-04-12 15:07:27','This lesson introduces you to several additional intellectual tools useful in making decisions about responsibility. When you have completed the lesson, you should be able to use these ideas in evaluating, taking, and defending positions on issues of responsibility. ','How Can You Decide Among Competing Responsibilities?','','publish','open','closed','','how_can_you_decide_among_competing_responsibilities','','','2019-04-12 15:07:27','2019-04-12 15:07:27','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/how_can_you_decide_among_competing_responsibilities/',0,'resource','',0),(58,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:27','2019-04-12 15:07:27','Students create pinhole cameras to understand that light travels in a straight path. They describe the lines and shapes in a 19th-century photograph of a building and then use their pinhole cameras to trace the architecture of their school building.','Capturing Light: The Science of Photography (Beginning Level)','','publish','open','closed','','capturing_light_the_science_of_photography_beginning_level','','','2019-04-12 15:07:27','2019-04-12 15:07:27','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/capturing_light_the_science_of_photography_beginning_level/',0,'resource','',0),(59,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:27','2019-04-12 15:07:27','Students study an object from antiquity that was found in the sea off the coast of Italy in order to understand how conservators remove and prevent corrosion on bronze statues. They derive meaning from analyzing the pose of the statue. Based on what they observe in the sculpture and what they read about the statue, students speculate about how the sculpture was lost at sea.','Fighting Corrosion to Save an Ancient Greek Bronze (Beginning Level)','','publish','open','closed','','fighting_corrosion_to_save_an_ancient_greek_bronze_beginning_level','','','2019-04-12 15:07:27','2019-04-12 15:07:27','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/fighting_corrosion_to_save_an_ancient_greek_bronze_beginning_level/',0,'resource','',0),(60,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:27','2019-04-12 15:07:27','In this activity, students explore the importance of charts to navigation on bodies of water. Using one worksheet, students learn to read the major map features found on a real nautical chart. Using another worksheet, students draw their own nautical chart using the symbols and identifying information learned.','Hands-on Activity: Nautical Navigation','','publish','open','closed','','hands-on_activity_nautical_navigation','','','2019-04-12 15:07:27','2019-04-12 15:07:27','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/hands-on_activity_nautical_navigation/',0,'resource','',0),(61,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:27','2019-04-12 15:07:27','A collection of videos and artifacts relating to the Red Planet. This collection was created to support the 2016 CCSSO Teachers of the Year Day at the Smithsonian.','Mars','','publish','open','closed','','mars','','','2019-04-12 15:07:27','2019-04-12 15:07:27','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/mars/',0,'resource','',0),(62,1,'2019-04-12 15:07:27','2019-04-12 15:07:27','This Learning Collection was developed to guide students in exploring the evolution of space suit design as a lead-in to NASA\'s recent Space Suit Design challenge. This is also being used as an example to showcase some of the features Smithsonian has added to their Learning Lab to allow educators the tools necessary to use open Smithsonian resources along with external materials to create digital learning experiences. ','Space Suit Design Challenge','','publish','open','closed','','space_suit_design_challenge','','','2019-04-12 15:07:27','2019-04-12 15:07:27','',0,'http://localhost.localdomain/resource/space_suit_design_challenge/',0,'resource','',0),(63,1,'2019-04-12 15:33:02','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','closed','closed','','','','','2019-04-12 15:33:02','0000-00-00 00:00:00'